      "x": 75,
      "y": 1555,
      "strokeColor": "#BF360C",
      "text": "\ud83d\udea8 NO-DEFAULT FITZPATRICK  (D-2026-05-19-012)",
      "fontSize": 15,
      "version": 1,
      "width": 363,
      "height": 18,
      "angle": 0,
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1165643691,
      "versionNonce": 1237660118,
      "index": null,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779179062089,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\ud83d\udea8 NO-DEFAULT FITZPATRICK  (D-2026-05-19-012)",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "autoResize": true,
      "customData": null,
      "baseline": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "mpcd9ydl9xc4m79vso8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 75,
      "y": 1580,
      "strokeColor": "#333333",
      "text": "Prototype pre-selected Fitz III; iOS does NOT.\nUser MUST tap a row before the verdict renders.\n\nWHY:  defaulting to III silently inflates the\nestimated safe time for Type I/II users by\n~50%  (MED_III / MED_I = 300/200 = 1.5\u00d7).\nThat is a one-way safety error.\n\nEmpty SkinType is a first-class state on\nNowView (\"Pick a skin type to see your\nestimate\"). Anchoring (Tversky & Kahneman\n1974) is real and asymmetric \u2014 over-estimating\nsafe time \u2192 erythema \u2192 melanoma risk.\n\nConvergent signal: Suchi + Linka + Wheeler.",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "version": 1,
      "width": 310,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 30319872,
      "versionNonce": 2112385588,
      "index": null,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779179062089,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Prototype pre-selected Fitz III; iOS does NOT.\nUser MUST tap a row before the verdict renders.\n\nWHY:  defaulting to III silently inflates the\nestimated safe time for Type I/II users by\n~50%  (MED_III / MED_I = 300/200 = 1.5\u00d7).\nThat is a one-way safety error.\n\nEmpty SkinType is a first-class state on\nNowView (\"Pick a skin type to see your\nestimate\"). Anchoring (Tversky & Kahneman\n1974) is real and asymmetric \u2014 over-estimating\nsafe time \u2192 erythema \u2192 melanoma risk.\n\nConvergent signal: Suchi + Linka + Wheeler.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "autoResize": true,
      "customData": null,
      "baseline": 9
    },
